  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project aims to assess the clinical and microbiological efficacy of fosfomycin(FOM) in
      patients with bacterial infection.

      Primary objective:

      • To assess clinical and microbiological efficacy of FOM in patients with bacterial
      infection.

      Secondary objectives:

        -  To determine the rate and severity of unexpected adverse events.

        -  To determine the mean duration of therapy with FOM in patients with bacterial infection.

      Study design:

      Multi-center, non-interventional study
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
